# Test-coverage output — the vitest/istanbul report directory at the repo ROOT.
#
# ANCHORED (leading slash) on purpose. Unanchored, `coverage/` matches a directory
# named `coverage` at ANY depth, which silently swallowed `src/coverage/` (the coverage
# MAPPER — source code) and then `src/__tests__/coverage/` (its tests). The mapper only
# survived because it was already tracked, and someone patched around the symptom with
# `!src/coverage/` rather than the cause. The tests were not so lucky: they were written,
# probed, and staged, and git dropped them without a word.
/coverage/
commit-message.txt
discovered-manifest.yaml

# MCPB build artifacts
*.mcpb
mcpb/server/
mcpb/bin/

# mcp-publisher login state (do not commit credentials)
.mcpregistry_github_token
.mcpregistry_registry_token

# Local MCP wiring — contains a real GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET
.mcp.json

# copied into the bundle by `make mcpb`
mcpb/LICENSE
mcpb/LICENSE-MIT
mcpb/NOTICE
